1
00:00:12,659 --> 00:00:15,787
<i>Urine tests were conducted</i>
<i>in schools nationwide</i>

2
00:00:15,870 --> 00:00:17,705
<i>under the ERPB's direction.</i>

3
00:00:17,789 --> 00:00:21,584
<i>The ERPB stated the tests were intended</i>
<i>to detect and treat at an early stage</i>

4
00:00:21,668 --> 00:00:25,380
<i>kidney abnormalities and diabetes-related</i>
<i>conditions among students.</i>

5
00:00:25,463 --> 00:00:27,215
<i>While some are questioning</i>

6
00:00:27,298 --> 00:00:31,136
<i>whether the tests are meant</i>
<i>to detect drug activity in schools,</i>

7
00:00:31,219 --> 00:00:35,098
<i>several schools have refused to take part,</i>
<i>citing final examinations.</i>

8
00:00:36,099 --> 00:00:38,434
<i>This is Seungyeon High School,</i>

9
00:00:38,518 --> 00:00:42,063
known as the most academically competitive
school in Gangnam.

10
00:00:42,147 --> 00:00:45,441
It also sends the most students
to SNU Medical School nationwide.

11
00:00:45,525 --> 00:00:47,610
You must know it well from living there.

12
00:00:48,194 --> 00:00:50,196
My mom wanted me to go to this school,

13
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:53,032
so my family moved nearby
when I was seven.

14
00:00:53,116 --> 00:00:54,617
Weren't you at a science school?

15
00:00:57,412 --> 00:01:03,251
Seungyeon High School is known
for having very pushy parents.

16
00:01:03,751 --> 00:01:07,005
CLASS S

17
00:01:10,008 --> 00:01:12,510
This is the last exam
that counts for early admission.

18
00:01:13,011 --> 00:01:15,430
If you blow this,
the CSAT is your only option.

19
00:01:15,513 --> 00:01:17,974
Unless you want that, do well today.

20
00:01:18,057 --> 00:01:19,142
Yes, sir.

21
00:01:19,225 --> 00:01:20,768
Okay, let's get started.

22
00:01:42,207 --> 00:01:44,626
Is it Class 1, Class 2, and then Class S?

23
00:01:45,210 --> 00:01:48,922
I told you this school sends
the most students to med school in Seoul.

24
00:01:49,005 --> 00:01:53,092
This is a special class
for those aiming for med school.

25
00:01:53,718 --> 00:01:57,680
It's basically a class
of the school's top students.

26
00:02:34,008 --> 00:02:35,635
My boy!

27
00:02:37,387 --> 00:02:39,889
Congratulations
on getting into SNU Medical School!

28
00:02:39,973 --> 00:02:41,599
-My son!
-Congratulations!

29
00:02:41,683 --> 00:02:42,809
This is huge!

30
00:02:43,393 --> 00:02:44,352
Congrats!

31
00:02:49,941 --> 00:02:50,942
Congrats!

32
00:02:54,654 --> 00:02:56,197
Hyeon-min, congrats!

33
00:03:12,213 --> 00:03:13,172
Who are you?

34
00:03:13,256 --> 00:03:15,591
-We're from the ERPB.
-Hey, are you okay?

35
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:32,275
His nose is bleeding.

36
00:03:32,358 --> 00:03:34,527
-Let's take him to the nurse's office.
-Okay.

37
00:03:35,445 --> 00:03:36,696
-Here.
-Let's get you up.

38
00:03:36,779 --> 00:03:38,531
Sir, where is the nurse's office?

39
00:03:38,614 --> 00:03:40,825
-Turn left, then go down.
-Left? Okay, thank you.

40
00:03:54,922 --> 00:03:55,923
-Here.
-Be careful.

41
00:03:56,007 --> 00:03:57,675
-Hold his head from the back.
-Okay.

42
00:04:08,478 --> 00:04:09,312
URINE TEST CHECKLIST

43
00:04:09,395 --> 00:04:10,313
Class 6…

44
00:04:10,396 --> 00:04:12,523
Stop the exam right now!

45
00:04:13,107 --> 00:04:15,068
My kid can't finish the exam!

46
00:04:18,613 --> 00:04:21,032
Do you want to see
my son and me die here today?

47
00:04:21,616 --> 00:04:23,993
Will you take responsibility
if he doesn't get in?

48
00:04:24,077 --> 00:04:26,287
Hyeon-min will take the exam
no matter what!

49
00:04:29,957 --> 00:04:31,584
-Jung Hyeon-min!
-Ma'am.

50
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:33,628
He passed out in the middle of the exam.

51
00:04:35,046 --> 00:04:36,589
How much did you get done?

52
00:04:39,842 --> 00:04:41,677
It's okay. There's still time.

53
00:04:41,761 --> 00:04:44,514
I already talked to the teacher,
so just finish the exam.

54
00:04:44,597 --> 00:04:46,057
Can you get up?

55
00:04:48,726 --> 00:04:51,646
Mom, I don't feel so good.

56
00:04:51,729 --> 00:04:54,482
It's from staying up all night studying.
Everyone's the same.

57
00:04:55,274 --> 00:04:56,109
Here.

58
00:04:57,443 --> 00:04:58,820
But Mom,

59
00:04:59,529 --> 00:05:01,197
I keep having weird thoughts.

60
00:05:02,448 --> 00:05:05,034
Weird thoughts while studying
mean you're losing focus.

61
00:05:07,078 --> 00:05:08,913
I've brought your medicine.

62
00:05:08,996 --> 00:05:10,289
You'll feel better soon.

63
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:13,543
Here.

64
00:05:18,214 --> 00:05:19,048
Here.

65
00:05:25,096 --> 00:05:26,681
You're almost there.

66
00:05:28,307 --> 00:05:31,436
You don't want all our hard work
to go to waste, do you?

67
00:05:32,103 --> 00:05:34,397
Hang in there, son. For me?

68
00:05:35,314 --> 00:05:37,066
All right, let's go.

69
00:05:58,671 --> 00:06:02,758
TEACH YOU A LESSON

70
00:06:08,556 --> 00:06:10,600
<i>Attention, students.</i>

71
00:06:10,683 --> 00:06:14,770
<i>There will now be an announcement</i>
<i>of special directives from the ERPB.</i>

72
00:06:14,854 --> 00:06:17,273
<i>All students are to remain on campus</i>

73
00:06:17,356 --> 00:06:20,902
<i>and prepare immediately for urine testing.</i>

74
00:06:25,823 --> 00:06:26,991
SON

75
00:06:30,953 --> 00:06:33,372
Hyeon-min, how did the exam go?

76
00:06:34,207 --> 00:06:35,500
Did you finish?

77
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,003
Why?

78
00:06:40,087 --> 00:06:41,547
What? The ERPB?

79
00:06:42,298 --> 00:06:43,674
They must be crazy.

80
00:06:44,175 --> 00:06:45,009
Okay.

81
00:06:45,092 --> 00:06:47,595
I'll head over to school now.
Call the other moms.

82
00:06:47,678 --> 00:06:49,096
What? The ERPB?

83
00:06:50,139 --> 00:06:52,808
Are they crazy?
The kids have to go to <i>hagwon </i>now.

84
00:06:55,937 --> 00:06:57,480
Where do you think you're going?

85
00:06:58,064 --> 00:06:59,732
Didn't you hear about the test?

86
00:06:59,815 --> 00:07:01,192
We're going to <i>hagwon</i>.

87
00:07:01,275 --> 00:07:02,443
Go after the urine test.

88
00:07:02,527 --> 00:07:04,529
Our moms are coming. You can talk to them.

89
00:07:04,612 --> 00:07:06,989
-What are they doing?
-What's the point of this?

90
00:07:07,073 --> 00:07:09,992
Da-hui, what are you doing?
You'll be late for <i>hagwon</i>. Get going.

91
00:07:10,076 --> 00:07:12,245
-You go ahead.
-What are they doing?

92
00:07:12,328 --> 00:07:14,580
-Go quickly.
-What the hell are they doing?

93
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:23,089
What do you think you're doing?

94
00:07:23,172 --> 00:07:26,509
-What do you think?
-Hyeon-min's mom, be quiet.

95
00:07:27,885 --> 00:07:31,097
Do you realize
how critical this period is for the kids?

96
00:07:31,931 --> 00:07:35,851
For top students, one point can move them
up or down several university tiers.

97
00:07:35,935 --> 00:07:39,855
There may be no guns, but students
and parents are fighting a war.

98
00:07:40,356 --> 00:07:42,692
So that's why you've put
lives on the line?

99
00:07:43,985 --> 00:07:47,321
You must've heard the rumors.
This test includes a drug screening.

100
00:07:48,072 --> 00:07:51,450
Drugs? Are you suggesting
our kids are on drugs?

101
00:07:53,953 --> 00:07:56,956
Those kids are applying
to SNU Medical School.

102
00:07:57,039 --> 00:07:59,959
-They're not like other kids.
-They all look the same to me.

103
00:08:01,919 --> 00:08:05,673
Have you even thought about what it took
for our kids to get this far?

104
00:08:06,799 --> 00:08:11,387
From birth through preschool,
elementary, middle, and high school,

105
00:08:11,470 --> 00:08:15,141
and now their most crucial year,
they have never wasted a single second.

106
00:08:15,224 --> 00:08:17,935
And what about the moms here?

107
00:08:18,436 --> 00:08:21,188
We sleep an hour less than our kids,
wake up an hour earlier,

108
00:08:21,272 --> 00:08:23,566
send them to <i>hagwon</i>, look for consultants…

109
00:08:24,817 --> 00:08:26,902
If you want them tested,
do it after the CSAT.

110
00:08:27,403 --> 00:08:30,781
Refusing the test will result
in a CSAT penalty. Is that okay?

111
00:08:30,865 --> 00:08:32,366
What do you mean "penalty"?

112
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:34,619
Are you threatening us
with our kids' lives?

113
00:08:34,702 --> 00:08:36,203
If I were, would you listen?

114
00:08:36,287 --> 00:08:37,955
This is Daechi-dong!

115
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,999
You think you can handle the moms here?

116
00:08:40,082 --> 00:08:40,916
Yes.

117
00:08:41,542 --> 00:08:42,793
The ERPB can handle them.

118
00:08:42,877 --> 00:08:43,919
Then go ahead.

119
00:08:44,003 --> 00:08:45,796
If you want to see people die.

120
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,215
We're doing the test so no one dies.

121
00:08:48,299 --> 00:08:49,800
So we can save even one life

122
00:08:50,509 --> 00:08:52,094
before it's too late.

123
00:08:54,305 --> 00:08:56,265
There's an ERPB-designated hospital.

124
00:08:56,349 --> 00:08:59,393
Take your children there for testing
before school tomorrow.

125
00:08:59,477 --> 00:09:00,770
If you don't,

126
00:09:02,313 --> 00:09:04,398
you won't be able to handle
what comes next.

127
00:09:13,282 --> 00:09:15,451
You're Jung Hyeon-min's mother, right?

128
00:09:17,578 --> 00:09:19,997
Hyeon-min didn't look very well earlier.

129
00:09:20,081 --> 00:09:22,291
Make sure you take him
for the test tomorrow.

130
00:09:36,138 --> 00:09:37,264
By any chance,

131
00:09:38,224 --> 00:09:39,600
do you know who I am?

132
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:43,062
Well, I've seen you on TV.

133
00:09:44,063 --> 00:09:46,482
You're someone very important.

134
00:09:49,276 --> 00:09:51,862
You hurt your hand
because of the EPRB, right?

135
00:09:51,946 --> 00:09:53,239
Oh, no.

136
00:09:53,322 --> 00:09:55,324
It was my fault.

137
00:09:55,408 --> 00:09:58,786
I'm not trying to blame the ERPB.

138
00:09:59,286 --> 00:10:01,288
I'm trying to help you.

139
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:03,916
Me? Why?

140
00:10:04,917 --> 00:10:07,628
Providing opportunities
to those who need them

141
00:10:08,212 --> 00:10:09,922
is my job as a politician.

142
00:10:11,841 --> 00:10:13,592
Can I look at your hand again?

143
00:10:15,511 --> 00:10:17,513
It doesn't look like a minor injury.

144
00:10:17,596 --> 00:10:19,348
How about treatment on the outside?

145
00:10:22,476 --> 00:10:26,856
<i>Recently, an armed attack broke out</i>
<i>in a juvenile prison.</i>

146
00:10:26,939 --> 00:10:29,984
<i>A juvenile offender</i>
<i>under the ERPB's supervision</i>

147
00:10:30,067 --> 00:10:32,653
<i>was attacked with a weapon by an inmate.</i>

148
00:10:32,737 --> 00:10:35,322
<i>It could have caused</i>
<i>serious harm or loss of life, but…</i>

149
00:10:35,406 --> 00:10:36,699
-What?
-Oh, nothing.

150
00:10:36,782 --> 00:10:38,284
<i>…the juvenile was unharmed.</i>

151
00:10:39,535 --> 00:10:42,747
<i>However, the inmate who protected him</i>
<i>was the perpetrator of…</i>

152
00:10:42,830 --> 00:10:44,039
-Where is it?
-Well…

153
00:10:44,123 --> 00:10:45,207
That way, sir.

154
00:10:45,291 --> 00:10:46,876
-Lead the way. Hurry up.
-Yes, sir.

155
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:49,044
<i>They deliberately chose where…</i>

156
00:10:49,128 --> 00:10:52,506
-I wonder where the toilet--
-You're making me more aware of it.

157
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:54,800
I already saw it all earlier.

158
00:10:55,301 --> 00:10:57,428
Look at you trying so hard.

159
00:10:57,511 --> 00:10:59,764
-Are you okay?
-Of course not.

160
00:10:59,847 --> 00:11:01,098
-That damn photo.
-Come on.

161
00:11:01,182 --> 00:11:02,600
-How did they get it?
-Let's go.

162
00:11:02,683 --> 00:11:04,643
Are the Seungyeon High kids being tested?

163
00:11:04,727 --> 00:11:06,562
Yes, they are.

164
00:11:13,986 --> 00:11:14,862
Need some air?

165
00:11:15,446 --> 00:11:16,322
Let's go outside.

166
00:11:24,330 --> 00:11:25,331
Drink this.

167
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:30,294
Are you okay? Feeling better?

168
00:11:30,377 --> 00:11:32,254
I'm feeling a bit better.

169
00:11:32,338 --> 00:11:33,297
Good.

170
00:11:37,802 --> 00:11:40,137
REPORT CARDS WERE DISTRIBUTED
TO STUDENTS TODAY

171
00:11:41,138 --> 00:11:42,431
Report cards are out.

172
00:11:42,515 --> 00:11:44,850
-They've also been sent by email. Check.
-Right.

173
00:11:57,279 --> 00:12:00,533
I passed out during the exam
for that subject.

174
00:12:03,577 --> 00:12:04,787
I'm sorry, Mom.

175
00:12:12,169 --> 00:12:13,921
What did I tell you?

176
00:12:16,006 --> 00:12:19,885
Kids like you who can't handle pressure
should at least take your meds properly.

177
00:12:21,512 --> 00:12:23,597
Is it really that hard to take your meds?

178
00:12:25,432 --> 00:12:27,601
Don't you feel sorry for me?

179
00:12:28,310 --> 00:12:31,522
I've had to swallow my pride
in front of the other moms because of you.

180
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:35,526
Did I ever ask for recognition?

181
00:12:37,236 --> 00:12:39,238
All I'm asking is for you to study.

182
00:12:42,157 --> 00:12:44,243
If you knew how hard I've worked…

183
00:12:47,288 --> 00:12:49,623
For God's sake…

184
00:13:20,779 --> 00:13:24,533
<i>Hyeon-min's goal is SNU Medical School.</i>

185
00:13:24,617 --> 00:13:29,038
I've heard you're a well-known consultant
for medical school admissions.

186
00:13:29,747 --> 00:13:33,375
I'll start by assessing his level.
How advanced is he in his studies?

187
00:13:34,501 --> 00:13:36,503
I've had him study ahead.

188
00:13:36,587 --> 00:13:39,924
He's in first year middle school
but is doing first-year high school math.

189
00:13:40,007 --> 00:13:42,801
He still hasn't finished high school math?

190
00:13:44,386 --> 00:13:46,180
He'll catch up soon.

191
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,058
Our Hyeon-min is top in his grade.

192
00:13:49,141 --> 00:13:53,020
A top student in a provincial school
becomes bottom-tier in Gangnam.

193
00:13:53,604 --> 00:13:55,648
Don't even think about med school.

194
00:13:57,232 --> 00:13:59,652
This isn't exactly the provinces.

195
00:13:59,735 --> 00:14:00,861
We're next to Seoul.

196
00:14:00,945 --> 00:14:02,905
You should meet my son first.
Once you do--

197
00:14:02,988 --> 00:14:04,865
Do you know when moms in Gangnam

198
00:14:04,949 --> 00:14:07,159
start preparing their kids
for SNU's med school?

199
00:14:09,119 --> 00:14:10,371
The moment they're born.

200
00:14:11,163 --> 00:14:13,791
They map out a 20-year plan,
from birth to med school,

201
00:14:13,874 --> 00:14:18,128
and choose preschools, schools, <i>hagwons</i>,
and private tutors accordingly.

202
00:14:18,212 --> 00:14:21,090
These kids have been preparing
for over a decade longer

203
00:14:21,173 --> 00:14:23,050
than those who start in middle school.

204
00:14:24,385 --> 00:14:25,970
By Hyeon-min's age,

205
00:14:26,053 --> 00:14:29,431
he should've already finished studying
the core concepts of the CSAT.

206
00:14:29,515 --> 00:14:32,476
He should be practicing questions
to avoid mistakes on the exam

207
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:35,854
and working on med school interviews,
essay writing, and English.

208
00:14:37,064 --> 00:14:41,068
Do you understand
just how far behind Hyeon-min is?

209
00:14:41,902 --> 00:14:44,029
Still, he's really…

210
00:14:45,698 --> 00:14:46,740
Kids in Daechi-dong

211
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:50,619
are tackling questions at this level
right now.

212
00:14:53,664 --> 00:14:54,832
How many of them

213
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:58,252
do you think Hyeon-min could answer?

214
00:15:16,145 --> 00:15:18,188
DAECHI SKY REAL ESTATE

215
00:15:20,149 --> 00:15:23,444
PRIME LISTING
A HOME THAT SENT KIDS TO SNU MED SCHOOL

216
00:15:23,527 --> 00:15:25,320
GRAND PRIZE IN ENGLISH, JUNG HYEON-MIN

217
00:15:26,572 --> 00:15:29,158
Do you really have to live
in a place like this?

218
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,995
It's within walking distance
of the school and <i>hagwon,</i>

219
00:15:33,078 --> 00:15:34,663
and a bargain for Gangnam.

220
00:15:34,747 --> 00:15:38,459
Besides, the two sons
who grew up here got into SNU.

221
00:15:38,959 --> 00:15:40,419
I even got it with no markup.

222
00:15:40,502 --> 00:15:42,629
I'm not sure about this.

223
00:15:42,713 --> 00:15:45,716
A school is a school.
This area can't be that special.

224
00:15:45,799 --> 00:15:47,342
You have no idea.

225
00:15:47,426 --> 00:15:50,721
Seungyeon High has a med school prep class
just for the top ten students.

226
00:15:50,804 --> 00:15:54,391
If you get into this class,
you're guaranteed SNU med school.

227
00:15:54,475 --> 00:15:56,852
Hyeon-min's goal
is to get into this class.

228
00:15:58,062 --> 00:16:00,898
But still, this place is just…

229
00:16:01,607 --> 00:16:03,317
Aren't you upset?

230
00:16:03,817 --> 00:16:05,736
Didn't your brother go to med school?

231
00:16:05,819 --> 00:16:08,530
Does your family treat you two the same?

232
00:16:08,614 --> 00:16:14,411
But thanks to him, I work at his clinic,
so don't be like that.

233
00:16:14,495 --> 00:16:17,289
That's exactly why
you and I get treated like that

234
00:16:17,372 --> 00:16:19,666
and why Hyeon-min does too.

235
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:22,294
I'll make sure
Hyeon-min gets into med school

236
00:16:22,377 --> 00:16:23,420
so he's respected.

237
00:16:23,504 --> 00:16:25,672
Who says he's not respected?

238
00:16:25,756 --> 00:16:27,341
That's enough!

239
00:16:28,550 --> 00:16:31,345
Don't be so discouraging.
Just take the door off.

240
00:16:31,887 --> 00:16:33,263
Fine, I will.

241
00:16:36,350 --> 00:16:37,726
I got it.

242
00:16:38,227 --> 00:16:39,686
Okay, hold it.

243
00:16:46,735 --> 00:16:49,488
GOAL
GET INTO SEUNGYEON HIGH!

244
00:16:53,117 --> 00:16:56,787
GOAL
GET INTO SNU MEDICAL SCHOOL!

245
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:12,594
Here.

246
00:17:13,971 --> 00:17:18,350
I'm not the only one making a fuss.
All the moms around here are like this.

247
00:17:19,434 --> 00:17:20,269
Okay.

248
00:17:21,353 --> 00:17:22,813
Oh, Mom.

249
00:17:23,313 --> 00:17:28,152
What about tutoring?
All the kids seem to have the same tutor.

250
00:17:28,944 --> 00:17:31,196
I'm looking into it, so don't worry.

251
00:17:31,738 --> 00:17:32,656
Keep studying.

252
00:17:38,912 --> 00:17:42,916
<i>Yeong-jun's mom, do you think</i>
<i>you can invite me to the moms' meetings?</i>

253
00:17:50,841 --> 00:17:51,675
Here.

254
00:17:52,426 --> 00:17:53,427
Enjoy.

255
00:17:54,803 --> 00:17:56,555
Forget about all the other moms.

256
00:17:56,638 --> 00:17:58,932
Just stay on Da-hui's mom's good side.

257
00:17:59,433 --> 00:18:00,726
She's the mama pig.

258
00:18:00,809 --> 00:18:01,977
The mama pig?

259
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:04,771
You know how a sow
has all her piglets following her?

260
00:18:04,855 --> 00:18:08,066
She has all the moms trailing after her,
so she's called the mama pig.

261
00:18:11,778 --> 00:18:14,615
But it's not something just anyone can do.

262
00:18:14,698 --> 00:18:17,075
Information is power for moms here.

263
00:18:17,701 --> 00:18:20,871
And Da-hui's mom has all the connections
with academic coordinators,

264
00:18:20,954 --> 00:18:22,831
admissions consultants,

265
00:18:22,915 --> 00:18:27,294
and even <i>hagwons</i>
with special programs for SNU med school.

266
00:18:27,377 --> 00:18:29,796
You're not a working mom, are you?

267
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:32,424
No, I'm not. Why?

268
00:18:32,507 --> 00:18:35,427
Working moms, or parents who both work,
can't join this circle.

269
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:40,307
They just take information and act busy
when it actually matters.

270
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:44,478
But doctors and professors
get a free pass no matter what.

271
00:18:45,062 --> 00:18:46,313
How come?

272
00:18:46,396 --> 00:18:49,816
You need a strategic student profile
for early admissions.

273
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:53,779
Hospital volunteer work
and university lab research

274
00:18:53,862 --> 00:18:56,406
make the ultimate student profile.

275
00:18:56,490 --> 00:18:59,243
With Da-hui's mom, it's a done deal.

276
00:19:01,078 --> 00:19:03,538
I'd better stay on her good side.

277
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:15,384
It's not bedtime yet.

278
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:16,635
I'm sorry.

279
00:19:17,135 --> 00:19:18,387
I was just so sleepy.

280
00:19:18,470 --> 00:19:20,681
You must be tired. Eat while you study.

281
00:19:22,182 --> 00:19:24,226
Can I have a little more?

282
00:19:24,309 --> 00:19:27,646
A full stomach makes you sleepy.
Your brain only needs glucose.

283
00:19:28,397 --> 00:19:31,817
Just eat this and focus a bit more.

284
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:32,734
Okay?

285
00:19:40,826 --> 00:19:42,202
Hi, honey.

286
00:19:44,246 --> 00:19:47,457
We're already here,
and you live by yourself.

287
00:19:47,541 --> 00:19:51,336
You can move to a cheaper studio
or move in with your mother.

288
00:19:53,005 --> 00:19:55,173
It's all for Hyeon-min!

289
00:20:00,554 --> 00:20:02,264
Once he succeeds,

290
00:20:02,848 --> 00:20:04,266
it will all be worth it.

291
00:20:20,073 --> 00:20:21,867
I didn't want to come empty-handed.

292
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:24,077
I hope you like it.

293
00:20:25,829 --> 00:20:27,331
You didn't have to.

294
00:20:32,961 --> 00:20:35,213
I came to see you because--

295
00:20:35,297 --> 00:20:37,758
Every mom comes to see me
for the same reason.

296
00:20:37,841 --> 00:20:39,718
And I already heard from Yeong-jun's mom.

297
00:20:40,594 --> 00:20:44,097
Just come to a few of our meetings
and see how it goes.

298
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:47,184
Okay.

299
00:20:47,684 --> 00:20:49,269
Was it? Was it okay?

300
00:20:50,228 --> 00:20:51,271
What would you like?

301
00:20:51,355 --> 00:20:53,565
-I'll have an iced latte.
-A latte.

302
00:20:53,648 --> 00:20:56,026
-Double shot, please.
-Double shot? Okay.

303
00:20:56,109 --> 00:20:57,652
DOUBLE SHOT

304
00:20:58,487 --> 00:21:01,281
-This is already too much.
-This is only the start, okay?

305
00:21:02,157 --> 00:21:03,075
Here you go.

306
00:21:03,158 --> 00:21:05,118
Here's your latte.

307
00:21:05,202 --> 00:21:07,954
-She's a natural.
-Yeah, you're right. It's Da-hui.

308
00:21:08,038 --> 00:21:09,623
That's why she's at that level.

309
00:21:09,706 --> 00:21:12,334
For math, Ms. Jung Da-eun is the best.

310
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:15,253
She gets kids into SNU med school.

311
00:21:15,337 --> 00:21:16,588
MATH
JUNG DA-EUN

312
00:21:16,671 --> 00:21:18,924
One downside is
that her academic background isn't great.

313
00:21:25,847 --> 00:21:27,766
ENGLISH
OH BO-HYEON

314
00:21:31,311 --> 00:21:34,439
It's easier if you start
by calculating 6 choose 2.

315
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:36,066
What's 6 choose 2?

316
00:21:36,149 --> 00:21:38,318
Then what's 15 times 6?

317
00:21:38,402 --> 00:21:40,070
-90.
-That's correct.

318
00:21:40,153 --> 00:21:43,532
90 is correct. Try solving this one
and see if you understand.

319
00:21:43,615 --> 00:21:45,325
REPORT CARD
YEAR 1, SEMESTER 1, 2024

320
00:22:03,677 --> 00:22:05,011
Don't worry.

321
00:22:05,095 --> 00:22:07,472
They say grades
depend on how much parents put in.

322
00:22:07,556 --> 00:22:08,390
Go on.

323
00:22:14,646 --> 00:22:17,357
For God's sake.

324
00:22:22,362 --> 00:22:24,364
It turns out these plates come as a set.

325
00:22:24,448 --> 00:22:27,451
If I'd known, I would've brought
the whole set last time.

326
00:22:28,743 --> 00:22:29,995
You didn't have to.

327
00:22:31,705 --> 00:22:33,123
I heard about Hyeon-min.

328
00:22:33,206 --> 00:22:35,917
He didn't get into
the med school prep class again, right?

329
00:22:36,001 --> 00:22:42,466
I got him the tutor you recommended,
and he goes to the same <i>hagwon </i>as Da-hui,

330
00:22:42,549 --> 00:22:44,718
so I don't know what the problem is.

331
00:22:44,801 --> 00:22:48,346
Sitting at a desk for hours
doesn't guarantee good grades.

332
00:22:48,430 --> 00:22:50,265
Even with the same study time,

333
00:22:50,348 --> 00:22:54,728
some kids take in 100%,
while others only take in 50%.

334
00:22:55,228 --> 00:22:57,063
That's the difference in focus.

335
00:22:58,190 --> 00:23:00,609
Is there a tutor for that too?

336
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:06,740
There are things a teacher can help with
and things they can't.

337
00:23:09,868 --> 00:23:10,911
Hold on.

338
00:23:22,756 --> 00:23:25,175
Here, try giving him this.

339
00:23:25,675 --> 00:23:28,011
His focus will improve dramatically.

340
00:23:28,094 --> 00:23:31,723
Da-hui and her older brother took it,
and their grades went up.

341
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:56,706
Hyeon-min.

342
00:23:59,459 --> 00:24:03,838
I went through a lot to get this for you
so you can study better.

343
00:24:04,464 --> 00:24:07,926
I know you'd do so well
if you really got your head in the game.

344
00:24:08,009 --> 00:24:09,427
I hear this stuff is amazing.

345
00:24:09,511 --> 00:24:12,514
You'll focus better
and be less nervous during exams.

346
00:24:13,431 --> 00:24:15,850
All the kids around here take it.

347
00:24:24,901 --> 00:24:25,735
Drink this.

348
00:24:29,823 --> 00:24:32,033
<i>This is an illegal drug.</i>

349
00:24:33,868 --> 00:24:35,996
You all look like you already knew.

350
00:24:37,038 --> 00:24:39,958
It's an unapproved ADHD medication
in Korea.

351
00:24:40,041 --> 00:24:43,712
Yet it has already been circulating
discreetly among mothers

352
00:24:43,795 --> 00:24:45,088
because it's effective.

353
00:24:45,589 --> 00:24:46,506
I'm sure you know.

354
00:24:48,925 --> 00:24:52,554
In the urine tests,
the children tested positive

355
00:24:52,637 --> 00:24:54,472
for methylphenidate and atomoxetine.

356
00:24:54,556 --> 00:24:58,560
These two drugs
are only for high-risk patients

357
00:24:58,643 --> 00:25:00,895
and are very rarely prescribed together.

358
00:25:00,979 --> 00:25:03,315
In particular,
methylphenidate is classified

359
00:25:03,398 --> 00:25:06,359
as a controlled psychotropic substance

360
00:25:06,443 --> 00:25:08,528
under the Narcotics Control Act in Korea.

361
00:25:09,112 --> 00:25:12,449
This means taking it
without a prescription is illegal.

362
00:25:14,284 --> 00:25:18,788
It violates the Narcotics Control Act
and the Pharmaceutical Affairs Act,

363
00:25:18,872 --> 00:25:20,707
making it a criminal offense.

364
00:25:21,333 --> 00:25:22,167
It'll be okay.

365
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:24,044
Everyone here will be subject

366
00:25:24,711 --> 00:25:26,630
to police questioning.

367
00:25:29,674 --> 00:25:30,759
Inspector.

368
00:25:30,842 --> 00:25:31,676
Yes?

369
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,679
The test results for Jung Hyeon-min
are concerning.

370
00:25:36,014 --> 00:25:37,349
Hyeon-min's mom.

371
00:25:38,516 --> 00:25:40,602
Where did Hyeon-min's mother go?

372
00:25:40,685 --> 00:25:44,272
-Hyeon-min's mom? Where did she go?
-I think she went out that way.

373
00:25:44,356 --> 00:25:45,398
Maybe to the bathroom?

374
00:25:45,482 --> 00:25:47,484
<i>I heard Hyeon-min's grades have gone up.</i>

375
00:25:49,194 --> 00:25:51,613
He must have been really determined.

376
00:25:51,696 --> 00:25:52,989
He's completely changed.

377
00:25:53,073 --> 00:25:55,158
He seems to have gotten mentally stronger.

378
00:25:55,241 --> 00:25:57,911
I think he'll make it
into the med school prep class soon.

379
00:25:58,578 --> 00:26:01,039
Still, the competition is really intense.

380
00:26:01,539 --> 00:26:06,252
Do you know of any medicine
that's better than the one you gave me?

381
00:26:06,336 --> 00:26:07,295
Well,

382
00:26:07,379 --> 00:26:11,132
I could find out if I looked into it,
but that one should be enough.

383
00:26:12,050 --> 00:26:12,967
I see.

384
00:26:15,512 --> 00:26:19,307
<i>My child's grades improved</i>
<i>after taking ADHD medication.</i>

385
00:26:19,391 --> 00:26:23,812
<i>I'm looking for something more effective.</i>
<i>If anyone knows, please help.</i>

386
00:26:24,479 --> 00:26:27,023
<i>Could you tell me what medication he took</i>
<i>that improved his grades?</i>

387
00:26:27,107 --> 00:26:29,275
They're no help at all.

388
00:26:33,988 --> 00:26:36,616
<i>I have the meds</i>
<i>last year's top med school entrant took.</i>

389
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:37,867
<i>Do you want it?</i>

390
00:27:06,438 --> 00:27:08,148
You're from the forum, right?

391
00:27:08,982 --> 00:27:09,816
Yes.

392
00:27:35,175 --> 00:27:38,303
TIER 1

393
00:27:45,852 --> 00:27:48,188
Well done, my son.

394
00:27:49,314 --> 00:27:51,524
Can you get
into the med school prep class now?

395
00:27:51,608 --> 00:27:54,903
Yes, they told me
to join the class tomorrow.

396
00:27:57,197 --> 00:27:58,031
That's great.

397
00:28:01,034 --> 00:28:01,993
Well done.

398
00:28:12,295 --> 00:28:13,797
JUNG HYEON-MIN'S MOTHER

399
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:15,882
She's still not picking up.

400
00:28:15,965 --> 00:28:19,052
They found another substance
in Hyeon-min's system besides ADHD meds.

401
00:28:19,135 --> 00:28:20,470
It's in the Heart Pills too.

402
00:28:20,553 --> 00:28:21,513
What?

403
00:28:23,515 --> 00:28:25,600
The amount is almost a lethal dose.

404
00:28:26,601 --> 00:28:29,187
If he keeps taking it
or increases the dose,

405
00:28:29,270 --> 00:28:30,814
couldn't it be life-threatening?

406
00:28:30,897 --> 00:28:33,233
-That's right.
-"That's right"? It's not…

407
00:28:33,733 --> 00:28:35,151
Are you crawling or what?

408
00:28:35,652 --> 00:28:36,736
I'm on it, kid!

409
00:28:45,036 --> 00:28:46,204
Hyeon-min.

410
00:28:47,038 --> 00:28:48,122
It's not your fault.

411
00:28:49,374 --> 00:28:50,708
You just got unlucky.

412
00:28:51,334 --> 00:28:53,670
Early admission is out,
but you still have the CSAT.

413
00:28:53,753 --> 00:28:56,130
If you do well,
you can still get into med school.

414
00:28:59,592 --> 00:29:01,928
You can pull yourself together
and do this, right?

415
00:29:03,388 --> 00:29:06,933
I'll get you excused for field study,
so don't go to school.

416
00:29:07,016 --> 00:29:09,352
Just study at home until the CSAT.

417
00:29:09,435 --> 00:29:10,436
Okay?

418
00:29:15,567 --> 00:29:16,651
Mom.

419
00:29:18,361 --> 00:29:19,988
Can you get me the meds?

420
00:29:21,447 --> 00:29:22,282
Yes.

421
00:29:22,782 --> 00:29:24,284
Let's take the meds and study.

422
00:29:43,553 --> 00:29:44,554
Hyeon-min.

423
00:29:45,972 --> 00:29:46,806
Jung Hyeon-min!

424
00:29:51,853 --> 00:29:53,313
Hyeon-min, are you in there?

425
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:57,734
HIGH SCHOOL SENIOR INSIDE
DO NOT RING!

426
00:30:07,577 --> 00:30:08,828
Oh no.

427
00:30:15,835 --> 00:30:17,462
They won't let me in.

428
00:30:17,545 --> 00:30:19,088
All right, sir.

429
00:30:20,965 --> 00:30:23,051
-What did he say?
-They won't let him in.

430
00:30:24,928 --> 00:30:26,763
However I see it, it seems dangerous.

431
00:30:26,846 --> 00:30:28,973
You're not actually going to jump,
are you?

432
00:30:29,057 --> 00:30:31,309
-The kid might die at this rate.
-What?

433
00:30:35,772 --> 00:30:37,941
Oh my God, why are you up there?

434
00:30:38,608 --> 00:30:39,943
Hold that tight, okay?

435
00:30:41,486 --> 00:30:42,487
Oh my God!

436
00:30:44,739 --> 00:30:45,573
Wait.

437
00:31:07,261 --> 00:31:09,889
Wait, Hyeon-min! The ERPB is here.

438
00:31:22,193 --> 00:31:23,611
Inspector Im Han-rim!

439
00:31:23,695 --> 00:31:25,697
Are you all right?

440
00:31:26,739 --> 00:31:28,324
-What the…
-Hyeon-min!

441
00:31:28,408 --> 00:31:29,784
-Let go.
-No.

442
00:31:29,867 --> 00:31:32,286
-Give me the pills!
-No! Let go!

443
00:31:32,787 --> 00:31:34,330
No!

444
00:31:34,414 --> 00:31:36,332
-Take Hyeon-min to the hospital.
-Okay.

445
00:31:37,667 --> 00:31:39,627
No, you can't!

446
00:31:39,711 --> 00:31:41,587
-Let go. Hyeon-min!
-Come on!

447
00:31:42,296 --> 00:31:43,840
Let me go. Hyeon-min!

448
00:31:43,923 --> 00:31:45,717
Let me go. Hyeon-min!

449
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,805
Why are you taking Hyeon-min?

450
00:31:52,807 --> 00:31:55,351
Ma'am, do you know
what kind of medication this is?

451
00:31:57,103 --> 00:31:59,439
Some students call it
a pill that keeps them awake,

452
00:31:59,522 --> 00:32:01,065
helps them focus,

453
00:32:01,149 --> 00:32:03,735
treats ADHD, boosts their grades,

454
00:32:03,818 --> 00:32:05,570
and gets them into med school.

455
00:32:05,653 --> 00:32:07,071
But we call it

456
00:32:07,572 --> 00:32:09,240
a pill that kills people.

457
00:32:10,908 --> 00:32:12,702
We call it an illicit drug.

458
00:32:15,663 --> 00:32:17,999
-What do you mean "illicit drug"?
-Didn't you know?

459
00:32:19,459 --> 00:32:20,668
No.

460
00:32:21,252 --> 00:32:24,172
I just gave it to him
because I heard it helps with focus.

461
00:32:24,255 --> 00:32:25,423
Did you really not know?

462
00:32:25,506 --> 00:32:27,216
How could I have?

463
00:32:27,300 --> 00:32:29,719
This is the first time
I'm hearing that it's bad!

464
00:32:29,802 --> 00:32:31,554
Did you really not know?

465
00:32:32,430 --> 00:32:34,557
Did you really not see
the changes in Hyeon-min…

466
00:32:36,976 --> 00:32:38,519
after he started taking it?

467
00:32:47,445 --> 00:32:48,321
Hyeon-min.

468
00:32:55,078 --> 00:32:56,746
Here, I got you. Oh my!

469
00:32:59,373 --> 00:33:01,000
I WANT TO DIE

470
00:33:01,084 --> 00:33:03,461
<i>You knew this drug</i>

471
00:33:04,003 --> 00:33:05,713
<i>was ruining Hyeon-min.</i>

472
00:33:25,191 --> 00:33:26,734
What were you thinking?

473
00:33:26,818 --> 00:33:28,653
As long as he could get into med school,

474
00:33:29,654 --> 00:33:32,365
you thought it was okay
to give him drugs like this?

475
00:33:33,825 --> 00:33:36,202
I was only going to give it to him
until the CSAT.

476
00:33:36,285 --> 00:33:39,080
Something could go wrong
with him before then.

477
00:33:39,163 --> 00:33:40,998
Is med school worth more than your son?

478
00:33:46,754 --> 00:33:48,548
I guess it is.

479
00:33:49,257 --> 00:33:50,925
He's almost there.

480
00:33:51,425 --> 00:33:54,470
Every second counts.
There's no time for this!

481
00:33:54,554 --> 00:33:56,722
Hyeon-min needs to study!

482
00:33:57,306 --> 00:33:58,391
From this moment on,

483
00:33:58,474 --> 00:34:01,185
you are not allowed
to leave this apartment.

484
00:34:01,269 --> 00:34:02,395
Why not?

485
00:34:02,478 --> 00:34:03,729
This is my home!

486
00:34:03,813 --> 00:34:05,481
This is to protect Hyeon-min.

487
00:34:05,565 --> 00:34:09,360
The ERPB will now separate
the child abuser from the victim.

488
00:34:09,443 --> 00:34:11,445
What do you mean "child abuse"?

489
00:34:11,529 --> 00:34:13,698
I'm his mother!

490
00:34:13,781 --> 00:34:16,909
I told you this is the most important time
of his life!

491
00:34:17,827 --> 00:34:21,622
Will you take responsibility
if he misses out on med school?

492
00:34:28,296 --> 00:34:30,381
If you want med school that badly,

493
00:34:32,258 --> 00:34:33,551
go yourself.

494
00:34:46,898 --> 00:34:48,399
Hyeon-min, are you okay?

495
00:34:50,776 --> 00:34:52,111
Oh my God, no!

496
00:34:54,739 --> 00:34:56,240
What are you doing?

497
00:34:57,700 --> 00:34:58,534
It's okay.

498
00:34:59,035 --> 00:34:59,869
Hyeon-min.

499
00:35:02,580 --> 00:35:05,333
Why put your hand there
when you have zero pain tolerance?

500
00:35:06,542 --> 00:35:09,170
It's better my hand gets hurt
than his head.

501
00:35:13,132 --> 00:35:15,509
Do you have a fever?
You're like a different person.

502
00:35:18,846 --> 00:35:20,181
Looking at Hyeon-min

503
00:35:20,681 --> 00:35:22,475
reminds me of my younger self.

504
00:35:23,059 --> 00:35:24,977
My mom tried to send me to med school too.

505
00:35:25,061 --> 00:35:26,687
So why didn't you go?

506
00:35:27,271 --> 00:35:29,232
Because it wasn't fun at all.

507
00:35:38,824 --> 00:35:40,785
CSAT PREP
SAMPLE QUESTIONS

508
00:35:43,162 --> 00:35:44,789
What are you trying to pull here?

509
00:35:44,872 --> 00:35:46,207
I told you.

510
00:35:46,958 --> 00:35:48,834
If you want med school, go yourself.

511
00:35:48,918 --> 00:35:51,837
Do you know why I want Hyeon-min
to go to med school?

512
00:35:52,922 --> 00:35:56,050
I have no connections.
Nothing to leave him either.

513
00:35:56,884 --> 00:35:59,845
When kids have to compete,
they end up resenting their parents.

514
00:35:59,929 --> 00:36:03,224
That's why you should study
and go to med school yourself.

515
00:36:03,307 --> 00:36:05,559
Then you can be his connection.

516
00:36:06,227 --> 00:36:07,895
Why do you want him to be self-made?

517
00:36:07,979 --> 00:36:09,814
He'd prefer well-off parents.

518
00:36:09,897 --> 00:36:12,149
How am I supposed to go to med school
at my age?

519
00:36:13,192 --> 00:36:15,194
I think you could if you stuck to this.

520
00:36:16,654 --> 00:36:17,530
These are

521
00:36:19,031 --> 00:36:23,119
the study and meal plans you made
for Hyeon-min.

522
00:36:23,703 --> 00:36:25,204
You planned it really well.

523
00:36:25,705 --> 00:36:27,456
If you stick to this,

524
00:36:27,957 --> 00:36:29,750
you could easily get into med school.

525
00:36:33,337 --> 00:36:34,213
Study.

526
00:36:34,797 --> 00:36:38,551
Once your mock exam scores
clear the med school cutoff,

527
00:36:38,634 --> 00:36:40,720
I'll let you see Hyeon-min.

528
00:36:42,471 --> 00:36:43,556
For God's sake!

529
00:36:44,598 --> 00:36:46,225
<i>17:30. Instead of going to </i>hagwon<i>,</i>

530
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:49,645
<i>work through the past CSAT English paper</i>
<i>at least three times.</i>

531
00:36:52,565 --> 00:36:55,151
<i>If you get even one question wrong,</i>
<i>start over.</i>

532
00:37:02,408 --> 00:37:04,577
It's not time to eat yet.

533
00:37:05,077 --> 00:37:07,204
<i>Nutritional support for brain function.</i>

534
00:37:07,288 --> 00:37:08,247
What's this?

535
00:37:08,331 --> 00:37:09,874
It's your dinner.

536
00:37:10,374 --> 00:37:11,709
Being full makes you sleepy.

537
00:37:12,335 --> 00:37:15,671
By the way,
I'm just following the meal plan.

538
00:37:20,718 --> 00:37:21,719
No? I'll take them.

539
00:37:22,595 --> 00:37:23,429
I'll eat them.

540
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:33,105
<i>After watching online lectures</i>
<i>and completing an error log,</i>

541
00:37:33,189 --> 00:37:34,190
<i>sleep at 1:00 a.m.</i>

542
00:37:39,653 --> 00:37:40,821
It's time to wake up.

543
00:37:44,075 --> 00:37:45,451
Let me sleep a little longer.

544
00:37:45,534 --> 00:37:48,162
Sleep four hours, you pass.
Sleep five, you fail!

545
00:37:48,245 --> 00:37:49,163
Oh man.

546
00:37:49,246 --> 00:37:50,122
So loud.

547
00:37:51,332 --> 00:37:52,333
Oh my goodness!

548
00:37:52,917 --> 00:37:54,335
What are you doing?

549
00:37:55,336 --> 00:37:57,963
I'm getting rid of this mattress
as it's distracting.

550
00:37:58,047 --> 00:38:00,216
Isn't that why you took this door off?

551
00:38:00,716 --> 00:38:02,051
Are you insane?

552
00:38:02,134 --> 00:38:05,679
Insane? Can't you see
that I'm sacrificing myself for you?

553
00:38:05,763 --> 00:38:07,723
More like fooling around.

554
00:38:08,682 --> 00:38:10,142
Does this look like a joke?

555
00:38:10,643 --> 00:38:14,438
Do you think I'd make you suffer the same,
and then one day say,

556
00:38:14,522 --> 00:38:19,443
"That's enough. Let's go see Hyeon-min
since you've learned your lesson"?

557
00:38:22,488 --> 00:38:24,240
That will never

558
00:38:25,157 --> 00:38:26,951
ever happen.

559
00:38:29,370 --> 00:38:33,124
There's only one way
you can leave this place.

560
00:38:34,667 --> 00:38:36,919
By getting into med school.

561
00:38:57,273 --> 00:38:59,608
You're up. Are you feeling okay?

562
00:39:01,735 --> 00:39:02,945
I'm sorry.

563
00:39:05,406 --> 00:39:07,032
You hurt your hand because of me.

564
00:39:08,909 --> 00:39:09,743
It's fine.

565
00:39:14,457 --> 00:39:15,332
What is it?

566
00:39:17,251 --> 00:39:18,085
Hey.

567
00:39:19,795 --> 00:39:21,630
Can you get me those pills?

568
00:39:22,506 --> 00:39:23,466
No.

569
00:39:24,300 --> 00:39:25,342
They're harmful.

570
00:39:27,011 --> 00:39:28,554
Harmful?

571
00:39:28,637 --> 00:39:30,097
It's an illegal drug.

572
00:39:35,519 --> 00:39:36,520
Can I just have one?

573
00:39:36,604 --> 00:39:37,938
-No.
-I swear it's the last.

574
00:39:38,022 --> 00:39:40,649
-No, Hyeon-min.
-I feel like I'll die without it!

575
00:39:40,733 --> 00:39:42,026
No. I said no!

576
00:39:42,526 --> 00:39:44,570
Do you think you can control it?

577
00:39:45,154 --> 00:39:48,282
Everyone says "just one" at first.
Then they say "just one more."

578
00:39:48,365 --> 00:39:50,409
That's how you ruin yourself.

579
00:39:50,910 --> 00:39:51,994
Your body,

580
00:39:52,077 --> 00:39:53,287
your mind,

581
00:39:54,455 --> 00:39:55,706
and even your life.

582
00:39:59,877 --> 00:40:02,630
If you don't want to die,
hold out until the end.

583
00:40:20,397 --> 00:40:21,690
You failed.

584
00:40:31,575 --> 00:40:32,493
Fail.

585
00:40:33,327 --> 00:40:34,411
You improved a little.

586
00:40:36,497 --> 00:40:37,540
Fail.

587
00:41:12,116 --> 00:41:14,868
STUDY SCHEDULE
JUST ONE MORE YEAR. YOU CAN DO THIS, SON

588
00:41:14,952 --> 00:41:17,788
GOAL
GET INTO SNU MEDICAL SCHOOL!

589
00:41:21,250 --> 00:41:23,335
I WANT TO DIE

590
00:41:36,849 --> 00:41:38,309
<i>I wanted to die.</i>

591
00:41:39,435 --> 00:41:41,520
I felt like the hell I was in
would never end

592
00:41:42,021 --> 00:41:44,231
unless I got into med school.

593
00:41:50,613 --> 00:41:53,907
Every time I felt like I wanted to die,
I took the pills.

594
00:41:58,787 --> 00:41:59,705
<i>Mom.</i>

595
00:42:00,748 --> 00:42:03,626
<i>Can I skip </i>hagwon <i>today?</i>

596
00:42:03,709 --> 00:42:05,586
<i>Why? What's wrong now?</i>

597
00:42:05,669 --> 00:42:08,213
<i>Those who hold out now</i>
<i>will be smiling later.</i>

598
00:42:08,714 --> 00:42:09,882
<i>You can do it, right?</i>

599
00:42:50,673 --> 00:42:52,508
Why did you skip <i>hagwon</i>?

600
00:42:56,512 --> 00:42:57,554
I'm sorry.

601
00:43:21,954 --> 00:43:23,747
<i>When I took the pills Mom got me,</i>

602
00:43:23,831 --> 00:43:26,333
<i>I didn't want to die anymore.</i>

603
00:43:28,127 --> 00:43:29,837
<i>But only for a moment.</i>

604
00:43:30,504 --> 00:43:33,799
<i>Soon after,</i>
<i>I felt like I wanted to die again.</i>

605
00:43:34,299 --> 00:43:37,136
Can you get me stronger pills?

606
00:43:39,805 --> 00:43:40,681
Okay.

607
00:43:42,182 --> 00:43:44,810
I took those pills
because I didn't want to die.

608
00:43:45,436 --> 00:43:47,896
Because I wanted to live.

609
00:43:50,858 --> 00:43:52,651
It's possible to live without them.

610
00:43:53,777 --> 00:43:56,822
Let's quit the pills
and anything that makes you feel suicidal.

611
00:43:57,948 --> 00:44:00,951
If it's studying, then quit studying.

612
00:44:02,077 --> 00:44:04,496
If it's med school,
then quit trying for it.

613
00:44:05,998 --> 00:44:07,249
And if it's your mom,

614
00:44:07,791 --> 00:44:09,084
quit your mom too.

615
00:44:16,008 --> 00:44:17,509
How would I quit my mom?

616
00:44:23,682 --> 00:44:25,809
That was a bit too much, wasn't it?

617
00:44:27,978 --> 00:44:28,812
Sorry.

618
00:44:45,078 --> 00:44:45,954
It's my birthday.

619
00:44:46,955 --> 00:44:48,081
Do you know when it is?

620
00:44:53,045 --> 00:44:54,296
Let me out.

621
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,423
It's too hard. I can't go on.

622
00:44:56,507 --> 00:44:58,884
So when it's too hard,
you just get to quit?

623
00:44:59,676 --> 00:45:01,178
You didn't let Hyeon-min do that.

624
00:45:01,261 --> 00:45:04,807
Do you really think
I was trying to kill my son?

625
00:45:04,890 --> 00:45:08,268
I sold a perfectly good home
and moved into this dump.

626
00:45:08,352 --> 00:45:11,939
I acted like a servant
to the moms just to get information.

627
00:45:12,022 --> 00:45:14,274
I got up early every morning
to make breakfast.

628
00:45:15,025 --> 00:45:17,152
I've never lived a day for myself.

629
00:45:17,736 --> 00:45:20,948
I couldn't even have a hobby
because I had to pay his <i>hagwon </i>fees.

630
00:45:21,031 --> 00:45:25,202
I did all this and sacrificed myself
so Hyeon-min could succeed.

631
00:45:27,412 --> 00:45:30,707
You didn't sacrifice yourself
for Hyeon-min.

632
00:45:31,208 --> 00:45:32,918
Hyeon-min…

633
00:45:35,921 --> 00:45:38,090
sacrificed himself for you.

634
00:45:47,015 --> 00:45:48,308
DRAW YOUR DREAM JOB

635
00:45:50,602 --> 00:45:52,229
NAME: JUNG HYEON-MIN
DREAM: DOCTOR

636
00:45:55,566 --> 00:45:58,569
Mommy would be so happy
if you became a doctor.

637
00:45:58,652 --> 00:46:01,488
-Really?
-Yes, of course.

638
00:46:01,572 --> 00:46:04,032
WHAT WILL YOU BE IN THE FUTURE?

639
00:46:04,616 --> 00:46:06,827
You should become a doctor, of course,

640
00:46:06,910 --> 00:46:08,912
and take care of me whenever I'm sick.

641
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:13,375
"Doctor."

642
00:46:14,084 --> 00:46:15,794
You're a good boy.

643
00:46:16,295 --> 00:46:17,588
You always listen to me.

644
00:46:18,171 --> 00:46:19,089
Yeah.

645
00:46:23,135 --> 00:46:25,053
Don't you feel bad for me and your dad?

646
00:46:25,971 --> 00:46:27,890
Why do you think we live like this?

647
00:46:27,973 --> 00:46:30,142
We're sacrificing for you.

648
00:46:30,809 --> 00:46:33,729
I'm sacrificing myself for you!

649
00:46:37,441 --> 00:46:38,692
Jung Hyeon-min!

650
00:46:39,192 --> 00:46:41,570
Do you think I enjoy this?

651
00:46:41,653 --> 00:46:43,572
I'm putting up with it for you.

652
00:46:43,655 --> 00:46:45,282
Mom, I'm sorry.

653
00:46:45,365 --> 00:46:48,535
If it weren't for you,
I could live a happy life.

654
00:46:48,619 --> 00:46:50,495
I'm sacrificing myself for you!

655
00:46:58,170 --> 00:47:00,631
<i>Ever since I was little,</i>
<i>Mom has always told me</i>

656
00:47:01,131 --> 00:47:02,841
<i>that I have to become a doctor.</i>

657
00:47:05,177 --> 00:47:08,221
<i>So I naturally thought</i>
<i>I should become one.</i>

658
00:47:13,310 --> 00:47:14,519
Sounds stupid, right?

659
00:47:19,441 --> 00:47:21,693
You said you did well in school, right?

660
00:47:22,569 --> 00:47:23,946
Nah, not really.

661
00:47:24,446 --> 00:47:27,282
Please tell me
what I'm supposed to do first.

662
00:47:30,786 --> 00:47:31,703
First,

663
00:47:32,204 --> 00:47:34,247
think about what you like the most.

664
00:47:35,540 --> 00:47:39,086
I'm happiest
when I do what I enjoy the most.

665
00:47:40,879 --> 00:47:44,216
I can name hundreds of things
my mom likes.

666
00:47:45,509 --> 00:47:47,594
But I can't think
of a single thing I like.

667
00:47:49,221 --> 00:47:50,555
What do I like?

668
00:47:54,935 --> 00:47:58,146
It's not too late to think about it.
Let's figure it out together.

669
00:47:58,772 --> 00:48:00,148
You too, Inspector Im.

670
00:48:03,402 --> 00:48:04,403
Just come on.

671
00:48:04,903 --> 00:48:06,113
Give me a second.

672
00:48:06,196 --> 00:48:08,407
I'm here for the books I asked for.

673
00:48:08,490 --> 00:48:09,449
Oh, yes.

674
00:48:09,533 --> 00:48:11,159
Pediatric center?

675
00:48:18,834 --> 00:48:20,043
Here, read these.

676
00:48:20,127 --> 00:48:21,253
KANG WON-MI THE JUDO GIRL

677
00:48:21,336 --> 00:48:23,088
-You know how old he is, right?
-Yeah.

678
00:48:23,922 --> 00:48:25,340
Here, you can read this.

679
00:48:25,841 --> 00:48:26,883
This is for you.

680
00:48:27,384 --> 00:48:29,302
-Come on.
-This is a children's book.

681
00:48:30,220 --> 00:48:31,471
You want me to read this?

682
00:48:31,555 --> 00:48:32,723
-Yeah.
-Me? It's for me?

683
00:48:32,806 --> 00:48:34,891
HAMSTER YAMMA WHO BECAME A YOUTUBER

684
00:48:41,023 --> 00:48:42,733
CHOI THE FIREFIGHTER CAT

685
00:49:29,362 --> 00:49:30,405
Get ready.

686
00:49:30,489 --> 00:49:31,823
We're going out.

687
00:49:45,212 --> 00:49:46,379
Hyeon-min.

688
00:49:49,091 --> 00:49:50,008
Are you okay?

689
00:49:50,092 --> 00:49:50,967
Yeah.

690
00:49:51,051 --> 00:49:52,344
Are you sure you're okay?

691
00:49:52,427 --> 00:49:54,096
I'm doing better.

692
00:49:57,641 --> 00:49:58,683
I'm glad to hear that.

693
00:50:01,478 --> 00:50:04,648
How are your studies?
You have been studying, right?

694
00:50:08,985 --> 00:50:11,321
I don't mean to pressure you,

695
00:50:11,404 --> 00:50:13,865
but the CSAT is coming up,
and I'm worried.

696
00:50:15,200 --> 00:50:16,618
You understand, don't you?

697
00:50:20,914 --> 00:50:22,207
Are you comfortable here?

698
00:50:22,707 --> 00:50:24,334
Is the food okay?

699
00:50:50,026 --> 00:50:50,861
Mom.

700
00:50:52,028 --> 00:50:53,029
Yeah?

701
00:50:54,906 --> 00:50:56,533
I have something to tell you.

702
00:50:57,284 --> 00:50:59,202
You do? What is it?

703
00:51:00,745 --> 00:51:02,247
I'm not going to med school.

704
00:51:02,873 --> 00:51:04,249
And I'm not taking the CSAT.

705
00:51:06,418 --> 00:51:07,335
What?

706
00:51:07,836 --> 00:51:09,504
I'll keep studying though.

707
00:51:10,005 --> 00:51:12,382
And I'll take the CSAT next year.

708
00:51:14,342 --> 00:51:16,511
But not this year.

709
00:51:17,012 --> 00:51:19,264
I don't want to live like this,

710
00:51:20,640 --> 00:51:22,934
aimless and doing what I'm told.

711
00:51:23,518 --> 00:51:24,895
I have no idea

712
00:51:25,687 --> 00:51:28,273
what you're talking about right now.

713
00:51:28,857 --> 00:51:29,691
Mom.

714
00:51:34,946 --> 00:51:36,698
Even if I don't take the CSAT

715
00:51:37,866 --> 00:51:39,201
or go to med school…

716
00:51:43,205 --> 00:51:44,789
I'm still your son.

717
00:51:46,124 --> 00:51:47,083
What are you--

718
00:51:47,167 --> 00:51:49,920
No matter what I decide,
please support me, Mom.

719
00:51:52,172 --> 00:51:53,590
No, Hyeon-min.

720
00:51:54,758 --> 00:51:56,551
You have to take the CSAT.

721
00:51:57,052 --> 00:51:58,595
You need to go to med school!

722
00:52:08,230 --> 00:52:09,773
I'm heading to my treatment now.

723
00:52:12,359 --> 00:52:14,027
No, Hyeon-min!

724
00:52:14,945 --> 00:52:15,862
No.

725
00:52:18,365 --> 00:52:20,700
I hope you stop suffering because of me

726
00:52:20,784 --> 00:52:23,495
and live your own life.

727
00:53:17,340 --> 00:53:21,094
In a recent inspection of all elementary,
middle, and high schools,

728
00:53:21,177 --> 00:53:25,515
many students tested positive
for ingredients from overseas ADHD drugs

729
00:53:25,598 --> 00:53:28,768
that are not approved domestically.

730
00:53:28,852 --> 00:53:30,103
In several cases,

731
00:53:30,186 --> 00:53:33,690
we detected a substance known
among parents and students as a study aid.

732
00:53:35,942 --> 00:53:36,901
This drug,

733
00:53:36,985 --> 00:53:40,864
also known as "Heart Pills,"

734
00:53:40,947 --> 00:53:43,408
contains designer drug components.

735
00:53:44,242 --> 00:53:47,162
In the future, the ERPB
will conduct screenings before the CSAT,

736
00:53:47,245 --> 00:53:51,541
and any student who tests positive
for illegal drugs

737
00:53:51,624 --> 00:53:53,001
will be disqualified.

738
00:54:04,471 --> 00:54:06,348
Are there this many types of drugs?

739
00:54:06,431 --> 00:54:09,351
They look different
but have similar ingredients.

740
00:54:10,060 --> 00:54:12,520
These Full Moon Pills
were popular about ten years ago,

741
00:54:12,604 --> 00:54:15,023
and these Snowman Pills
were popular five years ago.

742
00:54:15,106 --> 00:54:18,234
And these letters in the middle
were engraved by the dealers.

743
00:54:18,318 --> 00:54:21,279
They're like a trademark for a product.

744
00:54:22,447 --> 00:54:25,450
-These were popular two years ago--
-Excuse me.

745
00:54:28,286 --> 00:54:29,996
Could I take a quick look at this?

746
00:54:43,968 --> 00:54:46,179
We're fucked, damn it!

747
00:54:47,514 --> 00:54:48,932
What are we going to do now?

748
00:54:49,015 --> 00:54:52,769
Those fucking ERPB assholes
blocked everything.

749
00:54:57,732 --> 00:54:58,733
Isn't it obvious?

750
00:54:58,817 --> 00:55:01,361
The ERPB just needs to disappear,
doesn't it?

751
00:55:03,196 --> 00:55:05,323
WHAT SHOULD I DO… ABOUT GYU-CHEOL?

752
00:55:17,085 --> 00:55:21,714
WILL I EVER BE ABLE TO… FORGIVE GYU-CHEOL?

753
00:55:25,677 --> 00:55:27,595
CRACKDOWN ON GEN Z-TARGETED DESIGNER DRUGS

754
00:55:35,270 --> 00:55:38,022
<i>Gyu-cheol, let's say</i>

755
00:55:38,523 --> 00:55:42,444
your parole hearing goes well
and you're released back into society.

756
00:55:43,319 --> 00:55:45,113
What would you want to do most?

757
00:55:49,159 --> 00:55:50,160
<i>I'm not sure.</i>

758
00:55:50,869 --> 00:55:52,912
<i>I don't even dare hope for it.</i>

759
00:55:54,456 --> 00:55:58,001
But if it were possible…

760
00:56:01,045 --> 00:56:03,256
I'd want to go back to school.

761
00:56:05,675 --> 00:56:08,386
WILL I EVER BE ABLE TO… FORGIVE GYU-CHEOL?

762
00:56:08,470 --> 00:56:09,762
<i>Based on witness statements</i>

763
00:56:09,846 --> 00:56:14,976
<i>that the defendant, Cho Gyu-cheol,</i>
<i>showed ongoing hostility toward Ms. Choi,</i>

764
00:56:15,059 --> 00:56:19,147
we seek ten years' imprisonment
for premeditated retaliatory murder.

765
00:56:20,106 --> 00:56:21,357
It is clear

766
00:56:21,441 --> 00:56:23,818
Cho Gyu-cheol was changing
under Ms. Choi's guidance.

767
00:56:24,486 --> 00:56:27,655
This was nothing more
than a deeply unfortunate accident.

768
00:56:43,630 --> 00:56:44,589
Get on now.

769
00:58:00,039 --> 00:58:03,001
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

